.TH RANDOMWALLPAPER "1" "December 2025" "randomwallpaper 202511250713-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
randomwallpaper \- Set a random wallpaper
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B randomwallpaper
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,DIRECTORY\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B randomwallpaper
is a script for setting a random wallpaper from a directory of images. It automatically detects the desktop environment and uses the appropriate method to set the wallpaper.
.PP
The script can be used manually or scheduled via cron to change wallpapers periodically.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B randomwallpaper
Set a random wallpaper from default directory
.TP
.B randomwallpaper ~/Pictures/Wallpapers
Set random wallpaper from specified directory
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/randomwallpaper/settings.conf
User configuration file for randomwallpaper preferences
.TP
.B ~/Pictures/Wallpapers
Default wallpaper directory
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B RANDOMWALLPAPER_DIR
Override default wallpaper directory
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.TP
.B 3
No wallpaper images found
